## 5.0 Detailed Statistical and Evidentiary Analysis

### 5.1. Comparative Civic Character Scores

Descriptive statistics reveal two fundamentally different rhetorical profiles. McCain's speech is characterized by high scores in civic virtues, while Sanders' speech scores highly in both a key virtue (Justice) and several counter-virtues (Tribalism, Resentment).

| Speaker (Ideology) | Dignity | Tribalism | Justice | Resentment | Hope | Fear | Pragmatism | **Civic Character Index** |
